            <div class="description">
                <p>Fats occur naturally in food and play a significant role in human nutrition. Fats are used to store
                    energy in the body, insulate body tissues, cushion internal organs, and transport fat-soluble
                    vitamins in the blood. Fats also play in an important role in food preparation: They enhance food
                    flavor and food texture, make baked products tender, and conduct heat during cooking.</p>
            </div>
