            <div class="description">
                <p>Sterols, also known as steroid alcohols, are a subgroup of the steroids and an important class of
                    organic molecules. They occur naturally in plants, animals, and fungi, and can be also produced by
                    some bacteria (however likely with different functions).[1] The most familiar type of animal sterol
                    is cholesterol, which is vital to cell membrane structure, and functions as a precursor to
                    fat-soluble vitamins and steroid hormones.</p>
